   SeaWinds on QuikSCAT Level 3 Data
   Daily Ocean Wind Vectors
   (JPL SeaWinds Project)
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------
   ---------
   Data consists of gridded values of scalar wind speed, meridional and
   zonal components of wind velocity, wind speed squared and time given in
   fraction of a day. Data are currently available in Hierarchical Data
   Format (HDF) and exist from 19 July 1999 to present. More information
   on QuikSCAT L3 Daily Ocean Wind Vectors can be found here.


   QuikSCAT Sigma-0 Measurements
   BYU Daily Browse Images of QuikSCAT Sigma-0 Measurements (D. Long)
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------
   ---------
   Produced by Professor David Long at Brigham Young University, daily
   browse images made from QuikSCAT's Level 1B sigma-0 values are now
   available. These images can help select regions and time periods for
   studying not only winds but also land and ice. More information on this
   product can be found here.


   SeaWinds Near-Real-Time Animation
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------
   ---------
   The SeaWinds Daily Northeast Pacific wind movie. (QuickTime format,
   575Kb)
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------
   ---------
   For more SeaWinds animations, please visit the SeaWinds on QuikSCAT
   Daily Wind Report home page.


